{# TITLE: Scar Removal #}<p>Scars in patients are one of the most common reasons for seeking consultations with a plastic surgeon. Scar revision is what plastic surgeons do to improve the appearance of the scar.</p>
<p>Striclty speaking, one cannot &quot;remove&quot; a scar, but many &quot;tricks&quot; can be used to soften the appearance of it and to make it look less noticeable. Surgery and lasers can both be used for scar revision, but the actual method that is chosen by the plastic surgeon depends on the type, history, and the specifics of the scar.</p>
